e other day and I could just not beat him.  I wasn't taking advantage of hide, but he wasn't healing either just straight melee so we could work on our tactics.  The problem was I would maybe do slightly more damage but he had around 400hp more than me so it just wasn't enough.  Especially with me only getting two or three bs's in during the whole fight.  A little after that I fought a rogue of the same level and owned him but he also had about the same hp as me.  Should I just avoid straight melee encounters with tanks or am I doing something wrong?  The hp seem hard as hell to overcome.  After we were done really fighting we tried it out standing straight toe to toe, with him lowering his hp to only around 200 hp more than mine, then I completely owned him which isn't much of a surprise seeing as I have duel wield and I actually had three more ac than him.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Any adivce vs tanks would be appreciated. <p><hr>
<br>
