</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/01 8:56:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help fighting melees</span><hr size=1> I'd say that says something about his skill as a fighter then.  Since toe to toe (without moving I assume) you owned him, but running around and using tactics he beat you.  He may just be a better meleer than you.<br>
<br>
Aside from that possibility there are alot of things that come into play against melees.  Surprise is the first, and if you can get a poison snare or even dot off on them it will help immensely.  After that it's all about your technique (and some luck in landing good backstabs).<br>
<br>
I've fought higher level melee opponents that I beat b/c I landed great backstabs, and I've lost to a couple lower level people because all my landed stabs were horrible.<br>
 <p><FONT SIZE=2 FACE=Dauphin>The more you leave dead, the fewer blades will find your back.</FONT><BR><IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/loftness/Morvtwin2.JPG></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useanieconnerie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seanie Connerie</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/seanieconnerie/port.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/01 1:11:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help fighting melees</span><hr size=1> Well I practiced more today and was able to land quite a few more bs's than I had in the past.  A lot of it has to do with luck.  Now am I am finding the more I practice the better I am getting.(big suprise huh?) It is a lot easier for me to practice with a friend than with a dark because if it serious I am less willing to try new tactics.  I will just keep working on it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useanieconnerie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seanie Connerie</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/seanieconnerie/port.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 1/11/01 3:02:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoyoteblack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>coyoteblack</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/01 6:49:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help fighting melees</span><hr size=1>      Did you try mixing up different tactics. Circle strafe is great but if the pally knows of this he will spin with you. Try adding 2 more tactics<br>
<br>
Jousting: Timing the swing of that big one hander just stay out of range of it when it swings and jump and attack with you low delay weapons.<br>
<br>
Butterfly(figure <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> : I am still working in this one, it was bought to my attention from my brother obr members on Vallon. Start by cod but instead of a full circle stop half way and back up. seeing as the enemy is circling with you they will maneuver them selves into backstab position.<br>
<br>
Coyoteblack<br>
32nd Drunken Backstab<br>
Rallos OBR<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwiergraf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wiergraf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/13/01 11:38:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help fighting melees</span><hr size=1> I agree with Mordier, the outcome of a fight usually comes down to luck and technique, if you're both decent at melee.<br>
<br>
You could try instead of Circle Strafing, jumping through him and turning, to land a backstab hopefully before he can turn around. I usually use this since I still get disoriented when I use the circle strafing.<br>
<br>
Then there's poisons, potions, item effects, procs, ect. Or you could try staying close to them if they're medium or large sized to try and stay hidden merely by their bulk.<br>
<br>
That's about all I can think of right now. I've had precious few opportunities to hone my skills against other melees. <p><br>
<br>
