ocalUserPublicProfile?login=pageboy>Pageboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/14/01 2:41:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Heya Seanie</span><hr size=1> I know what yer talking about. Sometimes I can beat Slann pretty fast and sometimes I cant. Just depends on my backstabs. I joust sometimes with backstab (you can run through yer opponent and hit one), but usually I get hurt alot. Only way it seems i win is with poisons. I beat monks (and i hate them alot) by root poison. Blind is good too but when they run around its hard to hit them.<br>
<br>
I havent tried this one yet but if you could get a root off then back off and apply a blind. That would own. Haha  wanna try it in FV later??  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Cya in game Seanie.<br>
Pageboy Potbelly<br>
Tunare's Wardancers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/14/01 11:19:41 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/trinity.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heya Seanie</span><hr size=1> Well if you're really desperate, you can buy healing potions (about the price of pumice if I recall correctly) at your local herb shop (where pumice is also sold). Never sued one myself hehe, so I don't know if there is a casting time or if it's instanct, and whether or not you can make a 10 charge potion with them. When I get some cash I'm going to try it out though, as it'd be awesome to get down to a bubble then click my 10 charge potion a few times and get some health back.<br>
